summary.name: 2022 Tesla Model Y
summary.description: The Tesla Model Y is an all-electric vehicle manufactured by Tesla, Inc. It was first unveiled in March 2019, and its production began in January 2020 at the Fremont Factory. The Model Y was the fifth car produced by the company and is based on the Model 3 sedan which they share seventy-five percent of the same parts. In terms of performance and pricing Model Y falls between the model X and model 3. The vehicle has autopilot features and full-self driving. According to reports, the Model Y is one of the best-selling cars worldwide with 759,000 cars being sold last year. Tesla is continously shifting their headquarters, manufacturers and suppliers, therefore, this sheet contains supply chain information that is releveant to the US 2022 model Y.

overview.name: Tesla Headquarters/ Texas Gigafactory
overview.description: This is the main global headquarters for Tesla, Inc. In December 2021, CEO Elon Musk relocated the Tesla Global headquarters to the Gigafactory in Austin, Texas. Before this change, the corporate officers were located in Palo Alto, California. Therefore, this location contains Tesla's corporate offices and the Gigfactory, which serves as the manufacturing hub for the Model Y, Model 3, Semi, and the future Cybertruck.

overview.name: Nevada Gigafactory
overview.description: The Nevada Gigafactory focuses on the production of Lithium-ion batteries and battery cells. According to Tesla, the Nevada Gigafactory is “one of the world’s highest volume plants for electric motors" and produces a billion cells per year. https://www.tesla.com/giga-nevadaThere are currently 7,000 workers at this location and the company seeks to add more employees and expand the factory.

overview.name: Nickel
overview.description: For Tesla's batteries, one of the main components is Nickel and in 2021 Tesla signed a nickel supply agreement with BHP. BHP has headquarters in Australia. Tesla signed a five billion dollar agreement with BHP, and also has contracts with Vale S.A. and Trafigura for Nickel aquirement. Nickel is used in the batteries to provide a higher energy density and improve storage capacity. Tesla's batteries are made in-house at the Texas Gigfactory.

overview.name: Cobalt
overview.description: In 2021, Tesla signed a contract with Glencore, a Swiss Multi-national company with Mines across the Democratic Republic of the Congo. In the agreement, Tesla will buy up to 6,000 tons of cobalt per year.

overview.name: Lithium
overview.description: Lithium is another raw material that is essential to Tesla's battery production. In November 2021, Tesla signed a three year contract with Ganfeng Lithium Co and its unit company GFL International. The contract listed that Ganfeng would begin supplying Tesla with battery-grade lithium starting in 2022. T While the company has Headquarters in China, the lithium mines are located in Australia and Chile.

overview.name: 4680 Battery
overview.description: Tesla Model Y uses the company's 4680 lithium-ion battery. It is the first battery to be made in-house, as Tesla previously worked with CATL. The 4680 is primarily manufactured in the Texas/ Nevada Gigfactory and utilizes Nickel, Cobalt, and Lithium. The 4680 is Tesla’s fourth type of lithium-ion EV battery and offers a longer range and a more powerful performance than the other three.

overview.name: Fremont Factory
overview.description: The Tesla Fremont factory is a manufacturing facility in California. It was obtained by Tesla in 2010 and was previously owned by General Motors and Toyota due to their joint agreement. In July 2022, Tesla celebrated the production of its two millionth electric car produced in this facility.

overview.name: Factory Robotic Arms
overview.description: Tesla's production relies on both its workers and industrial robots. Tesla purchased more than 1,000 robot arms from Kuka and Fanuc. These robots are used through battery production, making the initial frame, and painting the car.

location.address: 6600 Center Drive, Sterling Heights, MI 48312, USA

overview.name: Body and chassis
overview.description: Tesla makes it's own body and chassis for its vehicles. For US cars, the body and chasis are fabricated in the Fremont Factory and Texas Gigafactory. Within these facilities, Tesla has some of the largest stamping machines in North America. Overall, this part entails the body panels of the car: door, roof, front, and back bumper. While the chassis is the overall frame that supports the vehicle.

overview.name: Headlight
overview.description: The Tesla model Y has convenience headlights that operate automatically based on driver activity. For example, they have low beam, high beam, auto high beam, and auto beam. Tesla recieves it headlights from Hella KGaA Hueck & Co which has Headquarters in Germany. The closest Hella location that is near a Tesla facility is in Palo Alto, California.

overview.name: Airbag
overview.description: While there is no public information about the airbag's Tesla uses in its car, upon tracking a serial number, Joyson Safety Systems came up as a possible provider.

location.address: Headquarters: 2025 Harmon Road Auburn Hills, MI 48326

overview.name: Ultrasonic Sensors
overview.description: Tesla uses ultrasonic senors to support its rear-view cameras which contribute to full-self driving and autopilot features. Ultrasonic sensors in the front and rear bumpers detect obstacles closer to the ground, and help identify surrounding cars. Tesla aquires it sensor from Omnivision a company with headquarters in Santa Clara and manufacturing in Shanghai.

location.address: US Headquarters: 4275 Burton Drive, Santa Clara

overview.name: Brake Calipers
overview.description: The performance and Long Range model Y use Brembo Break Calipers. Brembo is an Italian manufacturer of automotive brake systems; however, its nearest plant is located in Mexico. Brembo also supplies products for Abarth, Ford, Ferrari, Lamborghini, Alfa Romero and more. Its primary role is to slow the car's wheels by creating friction with the brake rotors.

location.address: 47765 Halyard Drive Plymouth, MI 48170 United States

overview.name: Sideview Cameras
overview.description: Tesla uses sideview cameras for the autopilot and full self driving features. In total, there are eight cameras on the outside and one camera on the inside of the vehicle. In 2022, Tesla secured a multibillion-dollar deal with Samsung Electro-Mechanics Co in agreements that the company would supply 80% of the units neccessary to operate autopilot. The other 20% is manufactured by LG Innotek.

overview.name: Front and Back Windshield
overview.description: The Tesla Model Y's Front and Back windshields are made with glass supplied by the American Glass Products (AGP) based in Germany. Working with Tesla is part of AGP's eGlass initiative, which aims to collaborate with "more than 20 automotive OEMs that are shaping the future of sustainable mobility."

overview.name: Center and dashboard Display
overview.description: Tesla has two main screen displays throughout their various models. There is a main display in the center of the car and a dashboard display. However, the model Y is an exception as it only include the main display, where drivers can use maps or other apps. AUO supplies these screens displays for Tesla. AUO also supplies products for companies like Ford, Toyota, and BMW.

location.address: 1 Lixing 2 Road Science Park East District Hsinchu, 30078 Taiwan

overview.name: Permanent magnet synchronous reluctance motor/ All Wheel Drive Motor
overview.description: Tesla makes its front and rear AWD motors. While Tesla does not provide much information about the manufacturing process of their motors, videos indicate that they are made in-house at all their major factories.

overview.name: Speaker System
overview.description: Tesla has various speakers in their vehicles. They allow users to play music, watch videos and even monitor the sound levels in the car. Tesla creates its own speaker system with the help of engineers from various backgrounds. The Tesla Model Y has a 13-speaker system that includes a 160-watt subwoofer and an amplifie.

overview.name: Leather Seating
overview.description: Tesla makes its own seating but sources the vegan-leather from Ultrafabrics.

overview.name: Union Pacific Railroad
overview.description: After the completion of the vehicle, Union Pacific Railroad is responsible for transporting cars produced at the Fremont factory to the East Coast.

location.address: El Paso, Texas, and Tucson, Arizona

overview.name: Tesla Showroom- Meatpacking district
overview.description: Unlike other vehicles, Tesla's are can not be purchased at a dealership. They can be ordered online or at the numerous service centers. Tesla has thousands of showrooms around the country so people can go on test drives or gain some experience with their cars.

overview.name: Tesla Service Center- Redhook
overview.description: Tesla has a sales and service center in Red Hook, Brooklyn. This location allows customers to Custom-build, purchase, pick up, and service their vehicles. This center is Tesla’s one of nine locations in New York state. Overall, Tesla has approximately 160 service centers across the United States.

overview.name: Tesla Supercharger-JFK
overview.description: Tesla has charging stations across the globe, and have approximately 7,000 chargers in the U.S. The superchargers have various charing speeds and are usually located by airports, shopping centers or rest stops.
